    • onAppointmentRadioSelection

      public void onAppointmentRadioSelection()
      On appointment radio selection. When a user selects a radio button on the appointment tab, the error UI messages are reset, thee filtered customer selection is cleared then the appropriate appointments are loaded based on radio button selection.

    • onFilterByCustomerSelected

    • onUpdateAppointmentClick

      public void onUpdateAppointmentClick(javafx.event.ActionEvent event) throws IOException
      On update appointment click. Checks to make sure an appointment is selected then if one is selected sends the user to the update window otherwise if an appointment is not selected an error is shown.
      Parameters:
      event - the event of the user clicking update appointment
      Throws:
      IOException - the io exception

    • onCancelAppointmentClick

      public void onCancelAppointmentClick()
      On cancel appointment click. Resets the UI error messages, then tries to check if an appointment is selected to cancel. If there isn't a selected appointment an error message is shown. If an appointment is selected then an alert is given to the user to confirm the cancellation.

    • onAddNewCustomerClick

      public void onAddNewCustomerClick(javafx.event.ActionEvent event) throws IOException
      On add new customer click. Opens the window to create a new customer
      Parameters:
      event - the event of the user clicking add.
      Throws:
      IOException - the io exception

    • onUpdateCustomerClick

      public void onUpdateCustomerClick(javafx.event.ActionEvent event) throws IOException
      On update customer click. Resets the UI error messages, then tries to check if a customer is selected. If a customer is not selected then an error message is displayed otherwise the user is redirected to a window to update customer data.
      Parameters:
      event - the event of user clicking update
      Throws:
      IOException - the io exception

    • onDeleteCustomerClick

      public void onDeleteCustomerClick()
      On delete customer click. Resets the UI error messages, then tries to check if a customer is selected to delete. If there isn't a selected customer an error message is shown. If a customer is selected then an alert is given to the user to confirm the deletion.

    • onScheduleReportClick

      public void onScheduleReportClick()
      On schedule report click. Checks that a contact is selected, if it's not empty a report of the contact's appointment schedule is displayed
